<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-DB448F10-8F69-44E8-9F3F-634038BEB41E" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-DB448F10-8F69-44E8-9F3F-634038BEB41E" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Description of the tile: "PQ health monitor"</b> </title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-12F673CD-B0D8-46B7-8607-19EFB042109A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Introduction</title><p class="- topic/p "> This tile shows traffic lights for all known and detectable print quality issues per customer print. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The information on this page is based on the graphs provided in the "Nozzle Performance" and "Media step Accuracy" tiles. Using specific scripting, all deviations shown in those graphs are analyzed and classified. Note that not all scripts are ready yet, so the number of columns will increase over time. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Basically, traffic lights can display four different colors. 
</p><table id="GUID-D0B9D198-EBB5-4B6B-B8D0-8A75DCA4E331" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="3.06*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Color 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Meaning 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">White 
</p><fig id="GUID-A73C50F4-52F6-404E-839B-E613FCFFF44A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AE8D9EAD-9313-4A8A-A4F2-1F09C3425CCB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE8D9EAD-9313-4A8A-A4F2-1F09C3425CCB-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Unable to detect 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Green 
</p><fig id="GUID-CB9FBD60-4644-4339-9FA5-DEC58E3D7688" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-401FB633-87EE-4995-9E84-66C6A1077016-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-401FB633-87EE-4995-9E84-66C6A1077016-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Everything is working well 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Yellow 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> There is deviation, which might be observable by the customer. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Red 
</p><fig id="GUID-C21B4278-F507-454F-9D70-5E207D6DA093" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-52CBB2A4-6A77-45FE-8C77-A9EEC9880F98-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-52CBB2A4-6A77-45FE-8C77-A9EEC9880F98-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The issue mentioned is definitely present in the customer print. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> The table is split in two sections. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The overall conclusion per section is highlighted in the column with the yellowish colour. (See figure below) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case this traffic light is Yellow or Red the next columns can be used to get more insights on the issue which causes this function to be out of specifications. 
</p><fig id="GUID-8BEB4167-3201-4BAF-B6F5-0F3595DECE71" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-CD0FD433-6ACA-4451-AB6B-6DA71A409929-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CD0FD433-6ACA-4451-AB6B-6DA71A409929-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">• For 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Media step performance 
</b>the column “Media step: Step within specification” represents the overall conclusion of the media step performance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">• The overall conclusion for 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Printhead performance</b> is the column “Printhead:Lowest PH Score” 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DF0F9B3B-F290-4EBD-B6CE-F7C296C15C68" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> The table below describes all individual columns including a link to a page on which the issue can be solved.</title><table id="GUID-AEC4567C-F8E9-4DB9-853A-D1C5329A507B" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.70*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="2.82*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Column 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Page to visit 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Media calibrated 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verifies if the media is calibrated by the user 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/tsm?tsm=TSM000295EN.US&amp;sessionid=1748343307021#!@$GUID-7F6E847A-CB2F-4EBF-94A0-1A4940D6E7BC.xml" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>White and/or dark lines in the first meter after the leading edge</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> X-tran calibrated 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verifies if the engine calibration of the X-tran is performed by the Field-engineer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/tsm?tsm=TSM000295EN.US&amp;sessionid=1748343307021#!@$GUID-9A056018-5643-4D8F-B52A-A9A0F14E2EC7.xml" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Lighter or darker areas every 11 cm</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Tension bar used correctly 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verifies if the profile is set correctly in relation to the usage of the tension-bar. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/tsm?tsm=TSM000295EN.US&amp;sessionid=1748343307021#!@$GUID-A47D785A-6A61-454A-B77A-E8D10016DB1C.xml" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?> Lighter areas every 50-70 cm</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Tension bar used correctly Markers used 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Verifies if the AAC-markers are used in the customer print 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Inform customer to use AAC-markers to improve media step performance 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Nozzleplate OK 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Checks if the nozzleplate on the C10-printheads (C1640/C1650) are still mounted correctly 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref href="GUID-12B44033-D3AA-4200-9447-36A691316DFC.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>04-T-001 Loose nozzle plate detected (inform the key operator/customer)</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="task" href="GUID-17E03B46-02EC-4F60-8364-45837BC8CE84.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Advanced technical views</linktext></link></linkpool><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-8EEAD3B4-0429-4FE3-B290-92E03CB47270.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>PQ Health monitor</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
